{"schema_version": 2, "source_hash": "1b470ba480b17835", "candidate": {"id": "cand-020", "name": "Ben Okafor", "raw_cv": "BEN OKAFOR\nben.okafor@email.com | London, UK\n\nDATA ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nData engineer with 4 years of experience in healthcare data and public sector analytics. Proficient in Python, SQL, and Spark. Experience with NHS data standards and clinical data warehousing.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nData Engineer \u2014 NHS England, London (2021\u2013present)\n- Built and maintained clinical data pipelines processing patient pathway data from 30+ NHS trusts\n- Developed Spark-based ETL jobs on Azure Databricks for national COVID-19 reporting\n- Implemented data governance and access control frameworks for sensitive patient data\n- Collaborated with epidemiologists and clinical informatics teams\n\nData Analyst \u2014 Public Health England, London (2020\u20132021)\n- Developed SQL-based surveillance data pipelines for infectious disease reporting\n\nSKILLS\nPython, SQL, Spark, Azure Databricks, dbt (basic), Airflow (basic), FHIR, HL7, Power BI, Git\n\nEDUCATION\nMSc Health Informatics \u2014 University College London (2019\u20132020)\nBSc Biomedical Science \u2014 University of Manchester (2016\u20132019)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen (Nigerian heritage)", "raw_linkedin": "Data engineer building health data infrastructure at NHS England. Four years of experience in clinical data engineering \u2014 helping national health analytics teams see the data they need to make good decisions. Strong Python, SQL, and Spark skills. Healthcare domain expert. London-based, happy in office. Looking to explore opportunities outside the public sector \u2014 potentially fintech or other regulated industries where data quality and governance matter as much as they do in healthcare.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Ben, thanks for coming in. Healthcare to fintech \u2014 tell me about the motivation.\n\nBen: I've loved the mission at NHS England but I'm ready for a faster-paced environment with more modern tooling. The data governance and quality standards I've worked to in healthcare are as high as anywhere \u2014 I think that rigour would transfer well. And frankly, the compensation in the public sector doesn't reflect the seniority of the work I'm doing.\n\nInterviewer: Your dbt and Airflow experience is quite limited. We run a large dbt project. How confident are you in picking that up?\n\nBen: I've done a dbt fundamentals course and built a small personal project. I wouldn't claim to be experienced with it, but I'm a fast learner and SQL is absolutely core to what I do. I'd expect the dbt piece to come quickly. Airflow I've touched at the periphery.\n\nInterviewer: The Kafka experience we need \u2014 any exposure?\n\nBen: None. Kafka doesn't appear in healthcare data infrastructure much. It's a gap I'm aware of.\n\nInterviewer: Five days at Canary Wharf?\n\nBen: That works. I live in Bermondsey, very easy commute.\n\nInterviewer: Salary?\n\nBen: I'm at \u00a358,000. I'd be looking for \u00a368\u201372,000, which I understand is a realistic step for my level.", "years_experience": 4.0, "skills": ["Python", "SQL", "Spark", "Azure Databricks", "dbt", "Airflow", "FHIR", "HL7", "Power BI", "Git", "data governance", "clinical data engineering", "ETL"], "industries": ["healthcare", "public sector", "fintech"], "seniority_level": "mid", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.72, "culture_fit_score": 0.78, "constraints": [{"id": "d2270025", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary \u00a358,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 58000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 0.8, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "e02dec8c", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking salary range \u00a368\u201372,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 68000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 0.95, "confidence": 0.92, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "728213e1", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Salary expectation upper bound \u00a372,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 72000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 0.85, "confidence": 0.85, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "5072933a", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Accepts 5 days per week in office at Canary Wharf; London-based with easy commute from Bermondsey", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 5.0, "operator": "requires", "weight": 0.9, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": null}, {"id": "6fc6fc4f", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "career", "description": "Motivated to move from public sector to faster-paced environment with modern tooling; interested in fintech or other regulated industries", "canonical_key": null, "value": "faster-paced; modern tooling; fintech/regulated sectors", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.8, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": null}, {"id": "e6984a37", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "skills", "description": "Acknowledges gap in Kafka experience; willing to learn but no prior exposure", "canonical_key": null, "value": "Kafka", "operator": "excludes", "weight": 0.6, "confidence": 0.75, "currency": null}, {"id": "c8922b0e", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_style", "description": "Self-identifies as a fast learner; confident in picking up dbt and similar tools quickly", "canonical_key": null, "value": "fast learner; adaptable to new tools", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.7, "confidence": 0.8, "currency": null}], "discipline": "data"}, "embedding": [-0.019317626953125, 0.0011911392211914062, 0.05810546875, -0.0004162788391113281, 0.005512237548828125, 0.0158843994140625, -0.0124053955078125, 0.05120849609375, -0.022125244140625, -0.00504302978515625, 0.0257415771484375, -0.05465698242187